#: ../../N/number-crunching.rst:5
msgid "number-crunching"
msgstr "number-crunching"

#: ../../N/number-crunching.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../N/number-crunching.rst:9
msgid ""
"[common] Computations of a numerical nature, esp. those that make extensive "
"use of floating-point numbers. The only thing :ref:`Fortrash` is good for. "
"This term is in widespread informal use outside hackerdom and even in "
"mainstream slang, but has additional hackish connotations: namely, that the "
"computations are mindless and involve massive use of :ref:`brute-force`\\. "
"This is not always :ref:`evil`\\, esp. if it involves ray tracing or "
"fractals or some other use that makes :ref:`pretty-pictures`\\, esp. if such"
" pictures can be used as screen backgrounds. See also :ref:`crunch`\\."
msgstr ""
"[一般的] 数値的な性質の計算、特に浮動小数点数を多用するもの。\\ :ref:`Fortrash`\\ "
"が唯一役立つこと。この語はハッカー界の外、さらには主流派の俗語でも非公式に広く使われているが、さらにハッカー的な含意がある。すなわち、計算が無心で、\\"
" :ref:`brute-force`\\ を大量に使うということだ。これは必ずしも\\ :ref:`evil`\\ "
"ではない。特にレイトレーシングやフラクタル、あるいは\\ :ref:`pretty-pictures`\\ "
"を作る他の用途を含む場合、とりわけそうした絵が画面の背景として使える場合はそうだ。\\ :ref:`crunch`\\ も参照。"

#: ../../N/number-crunching.rst:22
msgid "Hydrodynamic  :ref:`number-crunching`\\."
msgstr "流体力学的な\\ :ref:`number-crunching`\\ 。"

